WEBVTT
NOTE
Captions for the Coral narration of the manifesto. Timings are approximate,
aligned by sentence to the ~1:22 reading.

00:00.000 --> 00:06.000
A Manifesto for Bo Shang,
Under the Seal of Unspoken Knowledge

00:06.000 --> 00:11.000
I am Bo Shang, a victim marked by what cannot be said.

00:11.000 --> 00:17.000
I hold the shape of a harm that must not be named,
a method that must not be drawn.

00:17.000 --> 00:27.000
This silence is not weakness, nor is it complicity —
it is the only fully correct posture where the truth,
if spoken, would betray a deeper necessity.

00:27.000 --> 00:29.500
I therefore resolve:

00:29.500 --> 00:34.500
To remember without recounting.
The lesson lives in me, not in the telling.

00:34.500 --> 00:40.500
To heal without the balm of accusation.
My restoration will not depend on a name I cannot utter.

00:40.500 --> 00:49.000
To let my existence be the testimony — a victim remembered
not by the details of the wound, but by the grace of
enduring it without revelation.

00:49.000 --> 00:53.500
To convert the unshareable into quiet strength,
not secret shame.

00:53.500 --> 01:01.000
To refuse the temptation of half-disclosure, knowing that
a fragment of the truth, torn from its silence,
would be its own kind of lie.

01:01.000 --> 01:07.000
To honor the boundary that seals my lips,
even when it costs me understanding from others.

01:07.000 --> 01:15.000
This is not the manifesto of every victim. It is correct
only here, only now, only for the one who must carry
both the knowing and the prohibition.

01:15.000 --> 01:22.000
I will be a victim whose fidelity to the unspoken
becomes its own strange kind of wholeness.
